a)

Frvntade antalet fel: Gamla systemet

old <- rbinom(10000, size = 337, prob = 0.1)
evold <- mean(old)
print(evold)
## [1] 33.7585
hist(old, probability = TRUE) 
xfit <- seq(0, 337, 1)   
yfit <- dbinom(xfit, 337, 0.1)
lines(xfit, yfit, col="blue", lwd=2)

### Frvntade antalet fel: Nya systemet

newprob <- runif(10000, min = 0.02, max = 0.16)
evnewprob <- mean(newprob)
new <- rbinom(10000, size = 337, prob = evnewprob)
evnew <- mean(new)
print(evnew)
## [1] 30.1237

b)

P(frre fel i gamla systemet n nya) = intervallet [0.1, 0.16] / intervallet [0.02, 0.16] = 0.06/0.14 = 0.429

c)

sannolikheten att du kommer f fler n 50 fel i gamla systemet

p <- ecdf(old)
print(1-p(50))
## [1] 0.0017

sannolikheten att du kommer f fler n 50 fel i nya systemet

p <- ecdf(new)
print(1-p(50))
## [1] 2e-04

Uppgift 7 Monte Carlo metoder fr integrering

a)

montecarlocalcpi <- function(n) {

x <- runif(n, min = 0.0, max = 1.0)
y <- runif(n, min = 0.0, max = 1.0)

i <- 1
while (i <= length(x)) {
  eq <- (x[i]*x[i]+y[i]*y[i])**(1/2)
  if (eq > 1) {
    x <- x[-i]
    y <- y[-i]
  }
  else {
    i <- i + 1
  }
}

z <- length(x)

plot(x, y)

const <- 4 * z/n

return(const)
}
montecarlocalcpi(100)

## [1] 3.32
montecarlocalcpi(10000)

## [1] 3.1724
#montecarlocalcpi(100000)
#montecarlocalcpi(1000000)

b)

Vi frsker approximera pi, vilket verkar g ganska vl bde sett till talet man fr fram samt den grafiska kvartscirkeln.

c)

Approximationen blir exaktare, men berkningen tar mycket lngre tid.

d)

montecarlocalc <- function(n) {

x <- runif(n, min = 0.0, max = 2.0)
y <- runif(n, min = 0.0, max = 4.0)

plot(x,y)

return(mean(y < x**2)*8)
}

montecarlocalc(100000)

## [1] 2.67768

Uppgift 8 Stora talens lag

binomfunc <- function(n) {
  x <- rbinom(n, size = 10, prob = 0.2)
  return(x)
}

gammafunc <- function(n) {
  y <- rgamma(n, shape = 2, rate = 2)
  return(y)
}

a)

E[X] = size * prob = 10 * 0.2 = 2

E[Y] = shape / rate = 2 / 2 = 1 #RTK: alpha / beta allts: 2 / (1/2) = 2 * 2 = 4

b)

binomvector <- c()
draws <- c()

n <- 0
while (n < 10000) {
  if(n < 100) {
    n <- n + 10
  }
  else if (n < 1000) {
    n <- n + 100
  }
  else if (n < 10000) {
    n <- n + 1000
  }
  x <- mean(binomfunc(n))
  binomvector <- c(binomvector, x)
  draws <- c(draws, n)
}

plot(draws, binomvector, type = "l")

gammavector <- c()
draws <- c()

n <- 0
while (n < 10000) {
  if(n < 100) {
    n <- n + 10
  }
  else if (n < 1000) {
    n <- n + 100
  }
  else if (n < 10000) {
    n <- n + 1000
  }
  x <- mean(gammafunc(n))
  gammavector <- c(gammavector, x)
  draws <- c(draws, n)
}

plot(draws, gammavector, type = "l")

Uppgift 9 Vntevrde och varians

exponentialfunc <- function(n) {
 x <- rexp(n, rate = 10)
 return(x)
}

poissonfunc <- function(n) {
  y <- rpois(n, lambda = 3)
  return(y)
}

a)

E[X] = 1/rate = 1/10 = 0.1

Var[X] = 1/rate = 1/100 = 0.01

E[Y] = lambda = 3

Var[Y] = lambda = 3

b)

# Berknar E(X)
mean(exponentialfunc(10000))
## [1] 0.09927041
# Berknar Var(X)
var(exponentialfunc(10000))
## [1] 0.009971177
# Berknar E(Y)
mean(poissonfunc(10000))
## [1] 2.9908
# Berknar Var(Y)
var(poissonfunc(10000))
## [1] 3.038925

c)

  1. E(3) = 3
  2. E(3 * X + 2) = 3 * E(X) + 2 = 3 * 0.1 + 2 = 2.3
  3. E(X + Y) = E(X) + E(Y) = 0.1 + 3 = 3.1
  4. E(X * Y) = E(X) * E(Y) = 0.1 * 3 = 0.3
  5. E(3 * X + 2 * Y - 3) = 3 * E(X) + 2 * E(Y) - 3 = 3 * 0.1 + 2 * 3 - 3 = 3.3
  6. Var(2 * X - 5) = 2 * Var(X) = 4 * 0.01 = 0.04
  7. Var(X + Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y) = 0.01 + 3 = 3.01

d)

x <- exponentialfunc(10000)
y <- poissonfunc(10000)

#1
mean(3)
## [1] 3
#2
mean(3*x+2)
## [1] 2.292886
#3
mean(x+y)
## [1] 3.075729
#4
mean(x*y)
## [1] 0.2931294
#5
mean(3*x+2*y-3)
## [1] 3.249086
#6
var(2*x-5)
## [1] 0.03732443
#7
var(x+y)
## [1] 2.967211
